 show that $\\chi$ (photosphere\nheight to pressure scale height ratio) cannot be considered as a constant,\nconsistently with Watanabe et al. (2008). Comparisons with observations show\nthat all disk naturally evolve toward a shallow surface density disk ($\\Sigma\n\\propto r^{-1}$). The mass flux across the disk stabilizes in about 1 million\nyear typically.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Mar 2014 16:21:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-12"}
