ips, the zero-bias\ntransmittance as a function of the symmetric detuning yields two distinct\nbehaviors, in which one of them is unpredictable by the standard Fano's theory.\nTherefore, to access such a non trivial pattern of Fano interference, the\nhypothesis of the STM tip acting as a probe should be discarded.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Mar 2014 14:39:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-27"}
